{
  "texts": [
    "There are two approaches to service personalization.",
    "The discovery approach involves identifying and providing suitable services from the vast array of existing services in the market to each user, employing methods like recommendation systems for service suggestions [20].",
    "The development approach, on the other hand, entails creating new services tailored to user needs through development.",
    "However, developing finely detailed services that meet users' demands is not straightforward.",
    "Additionally, satisfying the individual requirements of many users necessitates the development of numerous services and features, which is impractical due to the enormous development costs involved."
  ]
}